<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xl-6 col-lg-8 col-md-9">

    <p>The National Species List is a resource of names, accepted, and other
       taxonomies for Australian native and naturalised taxa.
    </p>

    <p>Its current focus is on the names and taxonomies covered by the
       International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi and plants (ICN)
       and the International Code of Zoological Nomenclature (ICZN).
    </p>

    <p>The infrastructure for searching across these domains is currently in
       development.
    </p>

    <p>As names and taxonomic lists are made available in the NSL they will be available here. 
    </p>

  </div>
</div>
